![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5d56e145f80b7500016ba502/d1c43b75-29b1-49bf-b5d2-5962156e4918/20250224_135314.jpg?format=original)

In a recent interview with Fightful at the Elimination Chamber media junket, WWE Superstar Sami Zayn expressed his commitment to the company, hinting that he plans to stay with WWE for the foreseeable future.

When asked about his contract, Zayn responded "I'm usually kind of private about that stuff," he said, before adding, "I don't think I'm going anywhere."

Zayn, who has been an integral part of WWE's storyline in recent years, emphasized his satisfaction with his current role in the company. "I've got a good thing going here, and I see it continuing for the foreseeable future," he stated confidently.

While Zayn's comments do not provide explicit details about his contract status, they suggest that he is content with his position in WWE and plans to remain a key player in the company's future.